      "section_id": "s_5",
      "title": "Supplementary Fig. 7 | a) NMR chemical shift titration of $[ 1 3 0 , 1 5 \\mathsf { M } ]$ cCaM with 6-NBT.",
      "page_idx": 9,
      "body_text": "Chemical shift perturbations $( \\Delta \\delta )$ of $\\mathsf { H }$ (open symbols) and N (filled symbols) atoms of cCaM backbone amides K94 (circles), D95 (squares), V108 (triangles), V142 (diamonds), Q143 (hexagons), T146 (pentagons) and the sidechain amide of N111 (stars) were fitted globally to a 1:1 binding model with the shared $\\mathsf { K } _ { \\mathsf { d } }$ . The solid lines show the best fit with the $\\mathsf { K } _ { \\mathsf { d } }$ value of $1 . 0 \\pm 0 . 1 \\mathrm { \\ m M }$ . b) NMR chemical shift titration of $[ 1 3 0 , 1 5 \\mathsf { M } ]$ AlleyCat with 6-NBT Chemical shift perturbations $( \\Delta \\delta )$ of $\\mathsf { H }$ (open symbols) and N (filled symbols) atoms of AlleyCat backbone amides F89 (squares), E92 (triangles), I100 (diamonds), H107 (stars), and the sidechain amide of N111 (circles) were fitted globally to a 1:1 binding model with the shared $\\mathsf { K } _ { \\mathsf { d } }$ . The solid lines show the best fit with the $\\mathsf { K } _ { \\mathsf { d } }$ value of $3 . 3 \\pm 0 . 7$ mM. In both cases experiments were performed in $2 0 \\mathsf { m M }$ HEPES pH 6.9, 100 mM NaCl, 10 mM CaCl2 at $2 9 8 \\mathsf { K }$ .\n\nSupplementary Fig. 8 | CD spectra for representative myoglobin mutants (Mb-H64G/V68A, left; FerrElCat, right) in oxidized (black) and reduced (red) forms at pH 8.0 in the far UV (top) and the visible (bottom) regions.\n\nAlleyCat10 (blue) collected for $2 0 \\mu \\mathsf { M }$ proteins in 4 mM HEPES, 2 mM CaCl2, 30 mM NaCl (pH 7.0). Right: Chemical denaturation profiles of AlleyCat8 (black), AlleyCat9 (red) and\n\nAlleyCat10 (blue) obtained by monitoring the sample ellipticity at 222 nm at varying concentrations of guanidinium hydrochloride (GdHCl).\n\nSupplementary Fig. 10 | ITC titration curves and the corresponding binding isotherms for the titration of 1 mM 6-nitrobenzotriazole into $8 2 . 2 ~ \\mu \\mathrm { M }$ AlleyCat, 99.1 $\\mu \\ b { M }$ AlleyCat7, $9 9 . 2 ~ \\mu \\mathrm { M }$ AlleyCat8, $9 5 . 7 ~ \\mu \\mathrm { M }$ AlleyCat8-T146R, $1 0 3 \\ \\mu \\ M$ AlleyCat9, and $9 9 . 2 ~ \\mu \\mu$ AlleyCat10 in $2 0 \\ m M$ HEPES, 100 mM NaCl, 10 mM CaCl2 (pH 7.0), 2% acetonitrile at $\\yen 500$ . The data were analyzed in MicroCal PEAQ-ITC Analysis software (Malvern Panalytical) and the thermodynamic parameters were summarized in the Supplementary Table 6.\n\nSupplementary Fig. 11 | Uncut SDS-PAGE $( 1 5 \\% )$ gel images for the proteins used in this study.",
